<html lang="en"><head><meta charset="utf-8" /><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" /><title>FAQ - Adult Family Home</title><style>* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; } body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; } header { background-color: #2D5016; color: white; padding: 1rem 0; position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 100; } .header-content { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 20px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; } .logo { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: bold; } nav a { color: white; text-decoration: none; margin-left: 2rem; transition: opacity 0.3s; } nav a:hover { opacity: 0.8; } .container { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 20px; } h1 { color: #2D5016; margin-bottom: 2rem; text-align: center; } .faq-item { margin-bottom: 2rem; border-left: 4px solid #2D5016; padding-left: 1.5rem; background: #f9f9f9; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 4px; } .faq-item h3 { color: #2D5016; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-size: 1.1rem; } .faq-item p { color: #555; line-height: 1.8; } footer { background-color: #2D5016; color: white; text-align: center; padding: 2rem; margin-top: 3rem; font-size: 0.9rem; } .footer-contact { margin-bottom: 1rem; } .footer-contact a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; } .footer-contact a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }</style></head><body><header><div class="header-content"><div class="logo">Adult Family Home</div><nav><a href="/">Home</a><a href="/about">About</a><a href="/services">Services</a><a href="/faq">FAQ</a><a href="/news">News</a><a href="/contact">Contact</a><a href="/legal">Legal</a></nav></div></header><div class="container"><h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1><div class="faq-item"><h3>What is an adult family home and how is it different from assisted living or a nursing home?</h3><p>An adult family home is a small, licensed residential facility that provides personalized care in a home-like setting. Unlike larger facilities, we typically serve 4-6 residents, allowing for individualized attention and genuine family-style relationships.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>What services and levels of care are included?</h3><p>We provide personal care assistance, medication management, nutritious meals, 24/7 supervision, and social engagement activities. Care is tailored to each resident's individual needs.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>How much does it cost and what is included in the monthly rate?</h3><p>Costs vary based on the level of care needed. Our monthly rate includes room and board, all meals, personal care, medication management, and activities. Please contact us to discuss pricing.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>How is safety and supervision handled?</h3><p>Safety is our top priority. We provide 24/7 supervision, have secure spaces and proper lighting, and follow emergency protocols. For residents with dementia or mobility challenges, we use specialized approaches and equipment.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>What is daily life like?</h3><p>Daily life follows a calm, flexible routine with meals, activities, and outings. Family visits are always welcome. We carefully match compatible roommates and believe meaningful activities and relationships are essential to quality of life.</p></div></div><footer><div class="footer-contact"><a href="tel:425-123-4567">425-123-4567</a> | <a href="mailto:contact@afh.wamj@gmail.com">contact@afh.wamj@gmail.com</a> | 7am–7pm, 7 days a week</div><p>&copy; 2026 Adult Family Home. All rights reserved.</p><div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;"><a href="/" style="display: inline-block; background-color: #0066cc; color: white; padding: 8px 16px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-top: 1rem;">Back to Home</a></div></footer></body></html>
